cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.SOC

Reasoning: The paper discusses the diffusion of information, specifically memes, which can be related to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as it deals with the study of social networks and information diffusion. cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a possibility as the paper presents an upgraded Bass model to describe the diffusion dynamics of memes. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DL (Digital Libraries) are relevant as the paper discusses the citation history of scientific publications and the popularity of Wikipedia entries. Finally, cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) is another possible category as the paper explores the common mechanism behind the propagation of different memes.
